This paper deals with the evaluation and design of wireless communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also presents analytical expressions and approximations for statistical parameters, which involves mathematical analysis and modeling, making the paper relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Mathematical Analysis (cs.MA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper specifically focuses on the multihop Rayleigh fading channel, which is a topic related to Communication (cs.COMM) sub-category.
